betta fish i just bought a betta and have a question about feeding while i'm away i won't be away for long i plan to leave about lunch time on friday and will be back on sunday by supper time should i worry about not having anyone around to feed the fish on saturday my aquarium has a lid on it since i'm told male bettas can jump and i won't be able to put an automatic feeder in there don't worry bettas and most fish actually can go up to a week without food completely unharmed he will be fine if you leave him for the weekend don't feed extra before you leave eating too large an amount of food at one go can cause bloating and other digestive problems just feed his regular amount and then leave him without for two days i assure you he will not be harmed in any way by this automatic feeders usually don't work and can end up creating a big mess in your tank Betta (Siamese Fighting Fish) Sea-Monkey Daylight saving time Spirit rover timeline for 2004 March Breastfeeding Seabird Bowl Championship Series Lunch Weekend Major League Baseball television contracts Wheel of Fortune Dairy Friday Antarctic krill Stomach cancer Gar Discus (fish) Guinea pig Fish Finding Nemo Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Clownfish National Football League Aquarium Thanksgiving 2000 Australian Grand Prix Domestic rabbit Lent Albatross Fasting Goldfish Garfield Krill Sewage treatment Fishing Dietary fiber Spider Social rule Shaggy dog story Cuisine of Denmark Kibbutz Pizza Week 1957 World Series Poker jargon Timon and Pumbaa RuneScape quests Frog Biological pest control Hamster Dwarf gourami The Family from One End Street Eucharist Saturday ITV Sunday Jennings Randolph Lake Fish and chips Cafeteria Marine aquarium Sydney Riot of 1879 Ocean's Twelve Livestock Fahrenheit 9/11 Monday Night Football Little Shop of Horrors Environmental vegetarianism M60 machine gun MTV2 Gas metal arc welding Thermal power station Hurricane Katrina timeline Textile manufacturing Gastroparesis Orca Futurama 